<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-06-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-06-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="157" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d157">
                            <head>No. 157.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bolt</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Gaspé,
                                            Quebec</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-06-21"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 21,
                                        1872</date>. (Received June 21.)</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p rend="flushleft">Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamilton Eish</hi>:</p>
                            <p>The scandalous action of hoisting the Dominion flag over the
                                American, on the schooner James Bliss, is repeated this morning, and
                                remains so.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>GEO. HOLT, <hi rend="italic">Consul.</hi></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>